sources.description: This is a colorized and restored film about the Dutch city of Haarlem in The Netherlands more than a century ago in 1913. Note: The district of "Harlem" in New York was named after Haarlem when it was under Dutch control and called "New Amsterdam". Please view this film in HD (1080p). This film has been restored and colorized with state-of-the-art Artificial Intelligence software.
